text: Maria Martha Hacker Rocha (19 September 1936 – 4 July 2020) was a Brazilian model. She was the first winner of Miss Brasil in 1954, and the runner-up to Miss Universe. Rocha was born in Salvador, Bahia. Rocha was a breast cancer survivor. She died on 4 July 2020 from a heart attack caused by respiratory failure in Niterói, Rio de Janeiro, aged 83.Martha Rocha, 1ª Miss Brasil, morre em Niterói, no RJ ==References== Category:1936 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Brazilian models Category:Deaths from myocardial infarction Category:Deaths from respiratory failure Category:People from Salvador, Bahia
